13. Difference between Max Heap and Min Heap?
---------------------------------------------

Max Heap
--------

Parent >= Children

top() gives largest element.

Example:

50 40 30 20

top() = 50

Min Heap
--------

Parent <= Children

top() gives smallest element.

Example:

10 20 30 40

top() = 10

-----------------------------------------

14. Why is push() O(log n)?
---------------------------

New element is inserted at the bottom.

Then heap property is restored by moving upward
(heapify up).

Maximum movement:

Height of heap = log n

Complexity:

O(log n)

-----------------------------------------

15. Why is pop() O(log n)?
--------------------------

Root element is removed.

Last element moves to root.

Heap property restored by moving downward
(heapify down).

Maximum movement:

Height of heap = log n

Complexity:

O(log n)

=========================================
MOST COMMONLY USED FUNCTIONS
=========================================

push(x)       -> Insert element

pop()         -> Remove highest priority element

top()         -> Access highest priority element

empty()       -> Check if queue is empty

size()        -> Number of elements

=========================================
COMMON PROGRAM
=========================================

#include <iostream>
#include <queue>

using namespace std;

int main()
{
    priority_queue<int> pq;

    pq.push(10);
    pq.push(30);
    pq.push(20);
    pq.push(50);

    cout << "Top: "
         << pq.top() << endl;

    pq.pop();

    cout << "After pop Top: "
         << pq.top() << endl;

    cout << "Elements: ";

    while(!pq.empty())
    {
        cout << pq.top() << " ";
        pq.pop();
    }

    return 0;
}

Output:
50 30 20 10

=========================================
MIN HEAP PROGRAM
=========================================

#include <iostream>
#include <queue>

using namespace std;

int main()
{
    priority_queue<
        int,
        vector<int>,
        greater<int>
    > pq;

    pq.push(30);
    pq.push(10);
    pq.push(20);

    cout << pq.top();

    return 0;
}

Output:
10

